        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 3 at 4:10PM PDT by NWS Medford OR</headline>
        <description>At 410 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Worden, or 11 miles south of Klamath Falls, moving northeast at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Klamath Falls, Miller Island Klamath Wildlife Area, Midland, Moore
Park, Olene, Worden, and Altamont.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
